descr: "A statement of relationships from one set of concepts to one or more other concepts - either code systems or data elements, or classes in class models."

fields.name: mode
fields.descr: "Defines which action to take if there is no match in the group. One of 3 actions is possible: use the unmapped code (this is useful when doing a mapping between versions, and only a few codes have changed), use a fixed code (a default code), or alternatively, a reference to a different concept map can be provided (by canonical URL)."

fields.name: code
fields.descr: "The fixed code to use when the mode = 'fixed'  - all unmapped codes are mapped to a single fixed code."

fields.name: display
fields.descr: "The display for the code. The display is only provided to help editors when editing the concept map."

fields.name: url
fields.descr: "The canonical URL of the map to use if this map contains no mapping."
